'''Jindřich Staněk''' (born 27 April 1996) is a Czech professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Czech First League]] side [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] and the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career and time in England===
Staněk started his career with [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]], appearing on the bench for the first team on three occasions in 2013.<ref name="SW">{{Soccerway|jindich-stank/269907}}</ref> On 31 January 2014, he joined [[Premier League]] club [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] on a {{frac|2|1|2}}-year deal for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Transfer Deadline Day: Everton sign goalkeeper Jindrich Stanek|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/25984451|website=[[BBC Sport]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=31 January 2014|accessdate=20 March 2019}}</ref> On 29 September 2015, Staněk joined [[Hyde United F.C.|Hyde United]] on a one-month loan deal,<ref>{{Cite web|title=Hyde United snap up Everton goalkeeper Jindrich Stanek|url=https://www.tribalfootball.com/articles/hyde-united-snap-up-everton-goalkeeper-jindrich-stanek-4097790|website=Tribal Football|date=29 September 2015|access-date=20 March 2019}}</ref> going on to make five appearances for the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hydeunited.co.uk/player/jindrich-stanek/|title=Jindrich Stanek|publisher=[[Hyde United F.C.]]|access-date=20 March 2019|archive-date=14 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210414035648/https://hydeunited.co.uk/player/jindrich-stanek/|url-status=dead}}</ref> In June 2016, having made just two appearances on the bench for Everton,<ref name = 'SW'/> he was released by the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hitc.com/en-gb/2016/06/20/jindrich-stanek-reacts-on-twitter-to-everton-release/|title=Jindrich Stanek reacts on Twitter to Everton release|website=hitc.com|date=21 June 2016|accessdate=20 March 2019|archive-date=11 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170411191748/http://www.hitc.com/en-gb/2016/06/20/jindrich-stanek-reacts-on-twitter-to-everton-release/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===Return to the Czech Republic===
In September 2016, Staněk returned to the Czech Republic and signed for [[SK Dynamo České Budějovice|Dynamo České Budějovice]], later being sent on loan with [[HFK Třebíč|Třebíč]] in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dynamocb.cz/hrac.asp?id=Jindrich-Stanek-1116&sezona=2019&kategorie=MUZ|title=Jindřich Staněk|website=[[SK Dynamo České Budějovice]]|accessdate=20 March 2019|language=cs}}</ref> He made his [[Czech National Football League]] debut for České Budějovice on 24 September 2017 against [[FK Baník Sokolov]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Roman|last=Šperňák|title=Staněk hájí branku Českých Budějovic i reprezentace do 21 let|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/domaci-souteze/ceske-budejovice-jindrich-stanek.A171012_092412_fot_dsouteze_rou|website=[[Mladá fronta Dnes]]|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]|date=12 October 2017|access-date=24 July 2024|language=cs}}</ref>

Staněk joined [[FC Viktoria Plzeň|Viktoria Plzeň]] on loan in January 2020,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/prvni-liga/brankar-jindrich-stanek-hostovani-plzen-ceske-budejovice.A200108_124135_fotbal_min|title=Plzeň si pořídila odchovance Sparty, do brány bere Staňka|website=Mladá fronta Dnes|publisher=Mafra|date=8 January 2020|access-date=24 July 2020}}</ref> making his league debut in a goalless draw against [[FC Baník Ostrava|Baník Ostrava]] on 5 July.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Zdeněk|last=Soukup|title=Staněk po premiéře: Vychytaná nula potěší|trans-title=Staněk after debut: The picked-up zero will impress|url=https://plzensky.denik.cz/fotbal-prvni-liga/stanek-po-premiere-vychytana-nula-potesi-20200706.html|website=[[Mladá fronta Dnes]]|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]|date=6 July 2020|access-date=24 July 2024|language=cs}}</ref> He signed for the club permanently on 3 January 2021,<ref>{{Cite news|title=Plzeň začala i se Šulcem a Matějkou, na přestup získala Staňka|url=https://www.eurofotbal.cz/clanky/plzen-zacala-i-se-sulcem-a-matejkou-na-prestup-ziskala-stanka-487925/|url-status=dead|website=Eurofotbal.cz|date=3 January 2021|language=cs|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230206092045/https://www.eurofotbal.cz/clanky/plzen-zacala-i-se-sulcem-a-matejkou-na-prestup-ziskala-stanka-487925/|archive-date=6 February 2023|access-date=24 July 2024}}</ref> playing the entire [[2020–21 Czech Cup]] final against [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] on 20 May, which Plzeň lost 1–0.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Vítězný double pro Slavii. Pražanům triumf v poháru zajistil střídající Sima|url=https://sport.ceskatelevize.cz/clanek/fotbal/cesky-pohar/vitezny-double-pro-slavii-prazanum-triumf-v-poharu-zajistil-stridajici-sima/60a65ba1d60dfef4a4a19459|website=[[Czech Television]]|date=20 May 2021|language=cs|access-date=30 April 2025}}</ref> At the end of the season, Staněk was shortlisted for the Best Player Award together with [[Adam Hložek]] and [[Tomáš Holeš]], which Holeš went on to win.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Slávista Holeš byl zvolen nejlepším hráčem uplynulé ligové sezony, trenérské ocenění získal Bílek|url=https://www.irozhlas.cz/sport/fotbal/fotbal-ceska-liga-hrac-sezony-cena-holes-trener-bilek_2205151218_bac|website=[[Czech Radio]]|date=15 May 2022|language=cs|access-date=30 April 2025}}</ref> In July 2022, Staněk extended his contract with Viktoria Plzeň until 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Brankář Jindřich Staněk prodloužil až do roku 2025 smlouvu s FC Viktoria Plzeň|url=https://plzenska.drbna.cz/sport/fotbal/9423-brankar-jindrich-stanek-prodlouzil-az-do-roku-2025-smlouvu-s-fc-viktoria-plzen.html|website=Plzeňská Drbná|date=7 July 2022|access-date=29 January 2025|language=cs}}</ref>

On 5 January 2024, Staněk signed a contract with Slavia Prague until 2027 as part of a swap transfer with midfielders [[Lukáš Červ]] and [[Matěj Valenta]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Jan|last=Malý|title=Staněk se těší na výzvu ve Slavii, chce pomoct k titulu. V Plzni jsou Valenta a Červ|url=https://www.sport.cz/clanek/fotbal-ceska-1-liga-stanek-se-tesi-na-vyzvu-ve-slavii-chce-pomoct-k-titulu-v-plzni-jsou-valenta-a-cerv-5019472|website=[[Seznam.cz|Sport.cz]]|date=5 January 2024|language=cs}}</ref> He made his league debut for the club in a goalless draw against [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]] on 3 March 2024.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Jiří|last=    Čihák|title=Staňkův klidný debut na Letné: Málo práce? Po poháru toho měli všichni dost|trans-title=Staňek's calm debut at Letná: Little work? After the cup, everyone had enough|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/prvni-liga/jindrich-stanek-slavia-sparta-debut.A240303_213000_fotbal_jic|website=Mladá fronta Dnes|publisher=Mafra|date=3 March 2024|access-date=24 July 2024|language=cs}}</ref>

==International career==
Staněk represented [[Football Association of the Czech Republic|Czech Republic]] at every youth international level from [[Czech Republic national under-16 football team|under-16]] to [[Czech Republic national under-21 football team|under-21]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://repre.fotbal.cz/hrac/hraci/3735|title=Jindřich Staněk|publisher=[[Football Association of the Czech Republic]]|access-date=20 March 2019|language=cs}}</ref>

Staněk debuted for the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech senior squad]] on 5 September 2021 in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group E|2022 World Cup qualification]] against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]], ending in a 3–0 away loss.<ref name="IDNES 2021">{{Cite news|title=Nečekaný debutant v bráně. Pro mě výjimečný moment, škoda gólů, řekl Staněk|trans-title=An unexpected debutant in the gate. An exceptional moment for me, a shame about the goals, said Staněk|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/reprezentace/brankar-jindrich-stanek-belgie-cesko-kvalifikace-ms-2022.A210905_232443_fot_reprez_min|website=Mladá fronta Dnes|publisher=Mafra|date=6 September 2021|language=cs}}</ref> He entered the game in the 12th minute for the injured [[Tomáš Vaclík]], with the Czech Republic already down 1–0.<ref name="IDNES 2021"/> Staněk made his first start in the 1–1 draw against [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]] three days later.<ref>{{cite web|title=Česko - Ukrajina 1:1, dvě tyče Tecla, až pak gól. V nastavení srovnal Vydra|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/reprezentace/reprezentace-priprava-cesko-ukrajina-online.A210908_124209_fot_reprez_vp2|website=Mladá fronta Dnes|date=8 September 2021|access-date=28 October 2021|language=cs}}</ref>

On 29 May 2024, Staněk was included in the final Czech squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{Cite web|first=Ryan|last=Hancock|title=Czech Republic Euro 2024 squad: Ivan Hasek's full team|url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/czech-republic-euro-2024-squad-team-players-line-up-germany|website=[[FourFourTwo]]|date=21 September 2023|access-date=13 June 2024}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Outside football, Staněk also creates rap songs under the stage name Ejaytime.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Fotbal a rap? 7 fotbalistů, kteří si mimo české fotbalové trávníky vyzkoušeli i rap|url=https://www.ruik.cz/fotbal-a-rap-7-fotbalistu-kteri-si-mimo-ceske-fotbalove-travniky-vyzkouseli-i-rap/|website=Ruik|date=4 May 2020|access-date=20 May 2023|language=cs}}</ref>

